A.L.E: Arcade Learning Environment (version 0.5.1)
[Powered by Stella]
Use -help for help screen.

 ***************************************************************************
 * Welcome to A.L.E (Arcade Learning Environment)
 * (Powered by Stella)
 ***************************************************************************

 Usage: ale [options ...] romfile

 Main arguments:
   -help -- prints out help information
   -game_controller [fifo|fifo_named] (default: unset)
      Defines how Stella communicates with the player agent:
            - 'fifo':       Control occurs through FIFO pipes
            - 'fifo_named': Control occurs through named FIFO pipes
   -random_seed [n|time] (default: time)
     Sets the seed used for random number generation
   -display_screen [true|false] (default: false)
     Displays the game screen
   -sound [true|false] (default: false)
     Enable game sounds

 Environment arguments:
   -max_num_frames m (default: 0)
     The program will quit after this number of frames. 0 means never.
   -max_num_frames_per_episode m (default: 0)
     Ends each episode after this number of frames. 0 means never.
   -color_averaging [true|false] (default: false)
     Phosphor blends screens to reduce flicker
   -record_screen_dir [save_directory]
     Saves game screen images to save_directory
   -repeat_action_probability (default: 0.25)
     Stochasticity in the environment. It is the probability the previous action will repeated without executing the new one.

 FIFO Controller arguments:
   -run_length_encoding [true|false] (default: true)
     Encodes data using run-length encoding

 Misc. arguments:
   -ld [A/B] (default: B)
     Left player difficulty. B means easy.
   -rd [A/B] (default: B)
     Right player difficulty. B means easy.

No ROM File specified.
